item.title: Error: loaderror bobStarting up 20
item.dc:creator: @yppman yppman
item.description:
@yppman wrote:

Found the solution!! Ok dunno why the cache
is in use but it won’t hurt it to be deleted.
Use this to download a dos file manager I
uploaded, it can be used to delete the cache:
http://www.datafilehost.com/download.php?file=74939c59
Open the zip file and extract it to a folder.
Go to that folder and run dm.com.
Click the … at the top until one of the folders
shown is windows. Double click on that
and find MPR_FI~1. Click on it and click on
del at bottem of screen. Click yes. Your
Moparscape cache is now deleted. Now
Run moparscape, let it redownload cache,
and it should work!

Read full topic
